ce:section.ce:para:
The excitation wavelength-dependent emission properties of C-dots have been checked by fluorescence spectroscopy (Fig. 2 a) as a function of excitation wavelength ranging from 250 to 380 nm. By varying the excitation values, the maximum intensity was observed with λexc = 280 nm with the emission peak at λemi = 530 nm. Therefore, further fluorescence emission studies were carried out by using λexc = 280 nm. The emission intensity of C-dot has been found to be controlled by the greater number of particles getting excited at the particular wavelength. This behavioral variation was further associated with a quantum confinement effect and a surface passivation effect in the as-prepared C-dots from waste coconut coir. The quantum yield (
φ
) of as-developed C-dot system was found to be 48% as compared to Rhodamine B dye as reference dye. The stability of the prepared C-dots was further tested over a wide range of pH (2, 4, 6, 8, 10 and 12) (Fig. 2b).
